From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: 2026-05-23T19:15:00Z
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0052-uapi-ask-spdx-syscall-note.patch

PR14z21 (2026-05-23): fix UAPI SPDX identifier on
include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h so that `make headers_install` accepts it.

Symptom (CI run 26341035245, ask20 branch, FLAVOR=ask):

  HDRINST usr/include/linux/ask/ask.h
  error: include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h: missing "WITH Linux-syscall-note"
         for SPDX-License-Identifier
  make[5]: *** [scripts/Makefile.headersinst:63: usr/include/linux/ask/ask.h] Error 1
  make[4]: *** [Makefile:1382: headers] Error 2

Root cause: patch 0048-ask-in-tree-source-migration.patch creates the new
uapi header with

  /* SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0 */

The kernel uapi-header linter (scripts/headers_install.sh /
scripts/Makefile.headersinst, anchored on the recipe at
Documentation/process/license-rules.rst#L155 and enforced since
4.18) requires that every file under include/uapi/ carries the
syscall-note exception:

  /* SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0 WITH Linux-syscall-note */

without it, headers_install refuses to copy the header to
usr/include/, which bindeb-pkg invokes when building the
linux-headers .deb, breaking the whole kernel build.

The header has only just begun shipping in CI (PR14z19 / commit
17de07d landed patches 0044-0049 including 0048; all prior ASK
flavor builds were against an older patch stack that did not yet
create include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h, so this latent SPDX bug was
not exercised). Run 26341035245 was the first ASK build to apply
0048 and hit the lint.

Fix: replace the first line of include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h.
Authored as a follow-up patch instead of editing 0048 in place
to preserve 0048's blob hash and avoid touching line arithmetic
in a 6,900-line patch.

Signed-off-by: ci <ci@local>
---
diff --git a/include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h b/include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h
index 3debd51..7c0d8f1 100644
--- a/include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-/* SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0 */
+/* SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0 WITH Linux-syscall-note */
 /*
  * ASK2 generic-netlink UAPI.
  *
